    "course_title": "MARKETS AND MODELS",
    "description": "An investigation into the various ways that markets determine the allocation of scarce resources: via a single market-clearing price, waiting in line or other forms of rationing, search, a centralized matching algorithm, an auction, or a contest.  We will examine real-world examples of each type of market, and introduce and solve a formal theoretical model of each to see what insights it leads to.",
